# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Generated dataset output — images, labels, manifests.  Reproducible from
# scripts; never commit these.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
dataset/output/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# External datasets and third-party assets (user-downloaded; often multi-GB
# and under licences that forbid redistribution).
#   dataset/assets/            → CMU BVH, 100STYLE, AIST++, HDRIs, MPFB packs
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
dataset/assets/
dataset/logs/

# Same asset pool exposed under cherry_dataset_gen/ via a Windows junction /
# Linux symlink (see cherry_dataset_gen/README).  Walking the link resolves
# to ~41k BVH / HDRI / MPFB files — never commit these either.
cherry_dataset_gen/assets/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Training artefacts — checkpoints, TensorBoard event files, run configs.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
training/runs/
*.pt
*.pth
*.onnx
*.ckpt
*.safetensors
*.bin

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Python caches and build artefacts
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so
.Python
build/
dist/
*.egg-info/
.eggs/
.mypy_cache/
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Virtual environments
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
.venv/
venv/
env/
ENV/
.conda/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Editor / IDE / AI tool state
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
.vscode/
.idea/
.claude/
*.swp
*.swo

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OS cruft
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Blender
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.blend1
*.blend2
*.blend@

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Sim-to-real augmentation corpora — pre-extracted occluders, FDA refs,
# bg crops, and per-sample mattes.  Source: Open Images V7 (commercial-
# clean: images CC BY 2.0, annotations Apache-2.0).  Reproducible on the
# target machine via training/_iter_setup_openimages.sh +
# training/_iter_extract_openimages.py + training/_iter_compute_mattes.py.
# Total local footprint: ~3-5 GB (images cached to assets/openimages_raw/
# images_validation/ + extracted cutouts + bg crops).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
assets/sim2real_refs/
assets/openimages_raw/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Local capture footage — large, project-specific, not training data.
# (Small MediaPipe .task models stay tracked; bench scripts depend on them.)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
assets/*.mp4

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Generic binary bulk — rebuildable, not source.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.zip
*.tar
*.tar.gz
*.tgz
*.7z
*.rar
